From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenWrt <noreply@openwrt.org>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] net: airoha: qdma: call check_skb on all PPE hits

check_skb() is currently only called when the PPE returns reason
PPE_CPU_REASON_HIT_UNBIND_RATE_REACHED (0x0f).  Other PPE hit
reasons (e.g. INVALID entries after a disconnect) never trigger
check_skb, so bridge subflows that were invalidated by 990-02 are
never re-committed to hardware.

Fix by calling check_skb() for any packet the PPE provides a valid
hash for, regardless of the reason code.  The existing 100 ms rate
limit in check_skb() prevents excessive processing.

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt <noreply@openwrt.org>
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.c
@@ -970,7 +970,7 @@
 				     PKT_HASH_TYPE_L4);
 
 		reason = FIELD_GET(AIROHA_RXD4_PPE_CPU_REASON, msg1);
-		if (reason == PPE_CPU_REASON_HIT_UNBIND_RATE_REACHED)
+		if (hash != AIROHA_RXD4_FOE_ENTRY)
 			airoha_ppe_check_skb(&eth->ppe->dev, q->skb, hash,
 					     false);
 
